ad Max,' 'Parasite' and 'Inception' lead the way |last1=Montgomery |first1=Daniel | first2=Chris| last2=Beachum| first3=Marcus| last3=James Dixon| first4=Joyce | last4=Eng| first5=Zach| last5=Laws| first6=Susan| last6=Wloszczyna | date=February 25, 2020|website=[[Gold Derby]] |access-date=February 25, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Best Production Design\n| {{sortname|Paul|Denham Austerberry}}, {{sortname|Shane|Vieau}}, and {{sortname|Jeff|Melvin}}\n| {{pending}}\n|-\n| Best Makeup and Hairstyling\n| Mike Hill, [[Shane Mahan]], Jordan Samuel, and Paula Fleet\n| {{pending}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"7\"| [[Golden Globe Award]]s\n| rowspan=\"7\"| [[75th Golden Globe Awards|January 7, 2018]]\n| [[Golden Globe Award for Best Motion Picture \u2013 Drama|Best Motion Picture \u2013 Drama]]\n| ''[[The Shape of Water]]''\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"7\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|last=Respers |first=Lisa |url=http://www.cnn.com/2017/12/11/entertainment/golden-globe-nominations-2018/index.html |title=Golden Globe nominations 2018: The list |publisher=Cnn.com |date=December 11, 2017 |accessdate=December 11, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Golden Globe Award for Best Actress in a Motion Picture \u2013 Drama|Best Actress \u2013 Motion Picture Drama]]\n| {{sortname|Sally|Hawkins}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Golden Globe Award for Best Supporting Actor \u2013 Motion Picture|Best Supporting Actor \u2013 Motion Picture]]\n| {{sortname|Richard|Jenkins}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Golden Globe Award for Best Supporting Actress \u2013 Motion Picture|Best Supporting Actress \u2013 Motion Picture]]\n| {{sortname|Octavia|Spencer}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Golden Globe Award for Best Director|Best Director]]\n| {{sortname|Guillermo|del Toro}}\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Golden Globe Award for Best Screenplay|Best Screenplay]]\n| {{sortname|Guillermo|del Toro}} and {{sortname|Vanessa|Taylor}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Golden Globe Award for Best Original Score|Best Original Score]]\n| {{sortname|Alexandre|Desplat}}\n| {{won}