\n;[[Palm Springs International Film Festival]]\n|{{won|1}}\n|{{nom|1}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n;[[Producers Guild of America Award]]s\n|{{won|1}}\n|{{nom|1}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n;[[San Diego Film Critics Society]]\n|{{won|2}}\n|{{nom|8}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n;[[San Francisco Film Critics Circle]]\n|{{won|2}}\n|{{nom|9}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n;[[Satellite Awards]]\n|{{won|2}}\n|{{nom|10}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n;[[Saturn Awards]]\n|{{won|1}}\n|{{nom|9}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n;[[Screen Actors Guild Award]]s\n|{{won|0}}\n|{{nom|2}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n;[[Seattle Film Critics Society]]\n|{{won|0}}\n|{{nom|6}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n;[[St. Louis Gateway Film Critics Association]]\n|{{won|8}}\n|{{nom|12}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n;[[Toronto Film Critics Association]]\n|{{won|1}}\n|{{nom|1}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n;[[Vancouver Film Critics Circle]]\n|{{won|0}}\n|{{nom|1}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n;[[Venice Film Festival]]\n|{{won|4}}\n|{{nom|4}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n;[[Washington D.C. Area Film Critics Association]]\n|{{won|0}}\n|{{nom|7}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n;[[Women Film Critics Circle]]\n|{{won|0}}\n|{{nom|3}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n;[[Writers Guild of America Award]]s\n|{{won|0}}\n|{{nom|1}}\n|-\n|}\n|- style=\"background:#d9e8ff;\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" colspan=\"3\"|\n;'''Total number of awards and nominations'''{{efn|Certain award groups do not award only one winner, as they may recognize several recipients, and include runners-up. Since this is a specific recognition and is different from losing an award, runner-up mentions are considered wins in the awards tally.}}{{efn|Organizations without a Wikipedia page are not included in list of accolades.}}\n|-\n| {{won|'''Totals'''}}\n| {{won|'''90'''}}\n| {{nom|'''261'''}}\n|- style=\"background:#d9e8ff;\"\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"font-size: smaller; text-align:center;\" | [[#References|References]]\n|}\n\n''[[The Shape of Water]]'' is a 2017 American [[Romance film|romantic]] [[dark]] [[fantasy film]] directed and produced by [[Guillermo del Toro]]. Written by del Toro and [[Vanessa Taylor]], the film stars [[Sally Hawkins]] as a mute custodian at a high-security government laboratory during the [[Cold War]] in [[Baltimore]], where she befriends a captured humanoid-[[amphibian]] [[deep sea creature|sea creature]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2017/aug/31/the-shape-of-water-review-guillermo-del-toro-sally-hawkins-venice-film-festival-2017 |title=The Shape of Water review \u2013 Guillermo del Toro's fantasy has monster-sized heart |first=Xan |last=Brooks |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=August 31, 2017 |accessdate=December 17, 2017}}</ref> [[Michael Shannon]], [[Richard Jenkins]], [[Doug Jones (actor)|Doug Jones]], [[Michael Stuhlbarg]] and [[Octavia Spencer]] feature in supporting roles.\n\n''The Shape of Water'' premiered at the [[74th Venice International Film Festival]] on August 31, 2017,<ref name=\"InComp\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/venice-film-festival-unveils-lineup-74th-edition-1024415|title=Venice Competition Includes Films From George Clooney, Guillermo del Toro, Darren Aronofsky|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=July 27, 2017}}</ref> where it won the [[Golden Lion]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Guillermo del Toro's The Shape of Water wins Venice Golden Lion|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2017/sep/09/guillermo-del-toro-the-shape-of-water-golden-lion-venice-2017|work=[[The Guardian]]|publisher=Guardian Media Group|accessdate=September 9, 2017}}</ref> ''The Shape of Water'' received acclaim, with many critics declaring it del Toro's best film since ''[[Pan's Labyrinth]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://theplaylist.net/shape-of-water-review-20170831/|title=Guillermo Del Toro's 'The Shape of Water' Is Sweet & Scary Movie Magic [Venice Review]|publisher=[[The Playlist]]|author=Jessica Kiang|date=August 31, 2017|accessdate=September 7, 2017}}</ref> and particularly praising Hawkins's performance.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.indiewire.com/2017/08/the-shape-of-water-sally-hawkins-best-actress-oscars-2018-1201871825/|title='The Shape of Water' Reviews Rave About Sally Hawkins' \u2018Once-in-a-Lifetime' Silent Performance|work=[[Indiewire]]|author=Zack Sharf|date=August 31, 2017|accessdate=September 2, 2017}}</ref> In addition to the awards listed here, this was the first [[Academy Award for Best Picture|Best Picture Oscar]] win by a major studio in three years (''[[Birdman (film)|Birdman]]'', the previous such winner, was produced by the same studio as this particular film, [[20th Century Fox]]).\n\n== Accolades ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"width:99%;\"\n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\"| Award\n! scope=\"col\"| Date of ceremony\n! scope=\"col\"| Category\n! scope=\"col\"| Recipients\n! scope=\"col\"| Result\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"| {{Abbr|Ref.|References }}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"3\"| [[AACTA Awards|AACTA International Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"3\"| [[7th AACTA International Awards|January 5, 2018]]\n| [[AACTA International Award for Best Film|Best Film]]\n| ''[[The Shape of Water]]''\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/three-billboards-named-best-film-at-australian-academys-international-awards-1072157|title='Three Billboards' Named Best Film at Australian Academy's International Awards|first1=Gregg|last1=Kilday|first2=Alex|last2=Cramer|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=January 5, 2018|accessdate=January 6, 2018}}</ref><br><ref>{{cite web|url=https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/aacta-org/PDFs/2017/Media-Releases/7th-AACTA-International-Awards-Winners-Anno